James A. Long was named executive vice president in charge of the equity leveraged transactions group of Kleinwort Benson North America Inc., a newly created post at the U.S. unit of this London-based merchant bank.
He had been executive vice president of mergers and acquisitions at Primerica Corp. Separately, Marcus A. Hutchins was named president and chief executive officer of Kleinwort's Chicago-based futures brokerage subsidiary, Virginia Trading Corp.
He succeeds George P. Newman, who is leaving Virginia Trading to "pursue personal and community interests, including Ballet Chicago of which he is founder and president," the company said.
Mr. Hutchins has been executive vice president in charge of the funds-management business of Virginia Trading. 

